cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper deals with machine learning and fairness in algorithmic decision making, which are topics that are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses discrimination and sensitive attributes, which are relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm for discovering and eliminating discrimination patterns, which involves data mining and iterative refinement, making it relevant to the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
